info.name: Albedo
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Aphotic
info.lore: This dark relic was found at the very bottom of the deepest trench of the ocean. It drains all light surrounding it, blinding everything in a strange abyssal darkness.

info.name: Aries
info.lore: Two iron horns adorn this helmet to enhance the warriors of the Eradian, Dwarves who specifically rode Rams into battle at incredible speed.

info.name: Blue Mask
info.lore: The Blue Mask's physical traits are equal to that of paper, but the mystical properties enhance the wearers personal skills tenfold. The mask is thought to originate from an ancient Dernel tribe.

info.name: Bovine Killer
info.lore: This helmet was worn long ago by an infamous assassin who plagued Bovemist sites for decades. It was crafted of the still-bloody skin of their most prized and worshiped cows.

info.name: Call of the Void
info.lore: Originating from the unspeakable dark land, looking into the helmet will show nothing but darkness. Wearing it is said to reverse your morality, as if it were draining your will to live into the void.

info.name: Conflagrate
info.lore: Donning this helmet sears your mind with images of a world on fire. These blistering thoughts pressure you to make that world a reality.

info.name: Brise
info.lore: "With the hot, dry winds from the Roots and the cold, wet winds from Nesaak, these houses rot faster than you can blink." -Viraex, Elkurn Citizen

info.name: Butterfly
info.lore: "Time travel cares less about small things like a flapping wing, and more about big things, like becoming your own grandfather." -Martyn, Time Valley Resident

info.name: Cephalothorax
info.lore: "...Spiders have a weak point in the cephalothorax, essentially the neck. A small target, but it isn't as tough to chop through as the rest of them. ..." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3

info.name: Black Ripper
info.lore: "The skeletons at Ancient Nemract are rotted! is it even physically possible to rot a bone?" -Laen, Nemract Librarian

info.name: Fenmask
info.lore: This matted tangle of vines and marshland plants contains various herbal remedies woven into it. It is oddly comfortable, despite the thorns coating the inside.

info.name: Grillface
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] The old facemasks of the Eradian guards were forged from raw magma, and enchanted to remain searingly hot, so as to brand the wearer eternally with the mark of Rodoroc's elite.

info.name: Anima-Infused Helmet
info.lore: Engraved with the beauty and mystery of the boreal lights, this ornately-crafted crown is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Obsidian-Framed Helmet
info.lore: Made of dark minerals and adorned with pure obsidian, this ornately-crafted helmet is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Heliophilia
info.lore: This peculiar shawl is eternally warm to the touch, and shimmers brilliantly in the sunlight. It is rumored to give amazing health benefits and good fortune to those who wear it.

info.name: Little Inferno
info.lore: It is cold to the touch until worn. Once donned, it engulfs the wearer in excruciatingly hot flames, but never shall the wearer burn; only their enemies will feel the pain of the fire.

info.name: Blood Moon
info.lore: Imbued with the blood of the first werewolf, it was kept in Gelibord as a trophy before being stolen. Wearing it is said to mimic the effects of the lycanthropic curse.

info.name: Clearsight Spectacles
info.lore: Ancient magicks are required to make these brilliant glasses, imbued with charity and selflessness. They allow sight beyond sight, rumoured to allow sight of a brilliant realm.

info.name: Contest Wynner Cap
info.lore: I won!

info.name: Phoenix Prince's Crown
info.lore: The Phoenix Prince is a mythical figure spoken of in Avos legend. His crown cursed him in an endless cycle of death and rebirth.

info.name: Seekers Aid
info.lore: I found them!

info.name: Yellow Content Cap of Fame
info.lore: I helped!

info.name: Cancer
info.lore: 450 years ago a demonic plague like no other spread through Gavel, killing thousands. That is, until a priest encased the disease inside a helmet and warned everyone never to wear it.

info.name: Neolithic
info.lore: This ancient stone-hewn helmet is blended with the bones of an extinct animal of some kind. It is harder than dragon's hide.

info.name: Pelier
info.lore: Occasional whisperings can be heard by the wearers of this stone mask, reforged from a phylactery of souls. Although not dangerous, staring into the eyes of the mask can bring fear of one's soul being trapped within.

info.name: Pisces
info.lore: The oddly uncomfortable helmet was hand sculpted from a mystic clay found only in the depths of Molten Heights. Not much is known about the substance.

info.name: Gale's Sight
info.lore: True to their promise, these goggles were left as a memento for Ohms when his lover Gale finally died. Light as air, Gale's carefree nature lends itself to those who don them.

info.name: Shawl of Gaea
info.lore: Despite being thin enough to blow away in the wind, this mineral-blended shawl holds the force of a supervolcano within its soft fabric.

info.name: Shinespark
info.lore: There have been many attempts to create a reliable power system in Llevigar, and this plasma-charged helmet was reforged from a notable prototype.

info.name: Spectre
info.lore: The dark spectres of the decayed forests have created an insidious helmet to drain the spirit of those who wear it, and become servants to their dark whims. Many have fallen to its allure.

info.name: The Berserker's Helm
info.lore: Worn by a terrible berserker during his fanatical rampage through the land, his rage permeates this horned blackiron helmet.

info.name: The Forgery
info.lore: While only a mockery of the original product, this line of helmets became wildly popular before legal disputes and safety concerns halted production.

info.name: Third Eye
info.lore: The Bantisu monks have developed this enigmatic sigil in their years of meditation and study. It blesses the wearer with luck and powerful psionic ability.

info.name: Venison
info.lore: This ancient Elven sacrificial mask contains only a sliver of its previous magic, yet the blessing of the Elven god Entia still greatly empowers those who don it.

info.name: Dondasch
info.lore: The sheer bond between Adamastor and Urdar has manifested itself into a physical form due to their duress. Such power is not to be abused...

info.name: Marius' Prison
info.lore: "I know the Beast may return one day...but these chains shall bind it for eternity." The inscription glows bright in the darkness.

info.name: Adamantite
info.lore: Adamantite is a soft metal often added to exotic medicine to increase one's health, but a revolutionary blacksmith on Black Road, created a chestplate with an Adamantite alloy, which is advertised to bolster the users endurance.

info.name: Andesite Aegis
info.lore: Andesite is a stone commonly used for weapons and construction, but tends to be ineffective as armor when impure. This sturdy chestplate, however, is testament to the strength of pure andesite.

info.name: Aquarius
info.lore: The symbol of the river is a name that is often synonymous with this garment, with many water like qualities surrounding it, heavily bathed in magical meaning.

info.name: Augoeides
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Blessed Wrappings
info.lore: The thick, Bovemist-sanctified cloth is worn by their priests during certain religious ceremonies. It clears the mind and purifies the body.

info.name: Booster Plate
info.lore: A marvel of Corkus' electromagical advancements, this high-tech chestplate is equipped with steam jets to boost the user's speed, at a minimal cost to protection.

info.name: Cage of Bones
info.lore: The ancient bones of the demon Garaheth are stronger than steel. They clamp down when worn to constrict the bearer, inciting a slow madness.

info.name: Cardiac Arrest
info.lore: ...As the heart fails, adrenaline pumps through the body in an attempt to provide energy and keep the victim alive, but medical action must be taken to ensure survival. -Excerpt from Aldorei Medical Tomes, Vol. 6

info.name: Chimaera
info.lore: The one true Chimera in existence is sought by many, for great stories are told of its gifts to the worthy. One such gift was a simple fur coat, which gave the wearer but a taste of its power.

info.name: Garoth's Hope
info.lore: "Strangest thing, it turns out Creepers are incredibly flammable..." -Garull, Cryptid Researcher

info.name: Arakadicus' Body
info.lore: Long strips of chitin discarded from the mother of spiders Arakadicus still contain traces of her wicked powers, but few have survived the attempts to harvest them.

info.name: Ribcage
info.lore: "...as intimidating as the name sounds, you want your organs to be trapped in this kind of cage." -Excerpt from Human Anatomy For Fools, Cirh Nettan

info.name: Abdomen
info.lore: "...But under no circumstances should you stand directly behind an attacking spider. While not a universal trait, some spiders are capable of ejecting webs from their spinneret, leaving assailants and victims helpless." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3

info.name: Web Plate
info.lore: "I just need a little more spider silk to finish this vest!" -Lacrona, Detlas Tailor, found eaten by Nivla spiders

info.name: Dead Samurai's Plate
info.lore: "We get a lot of weirdos coming from Gavel by airship. That plate mail looked unusably ornate!" -Calo, Private Airship Operator

info.name: Erratio
info.lore: The blind prophet who crafted this macabre breastplate used the bones of only the most ruthless justiciars and executioners. Its wearers are supposedly destined to only die either a heroic or a just death.

info.name: Giant's Bracer
info.lore: This ill-fitting, bulky chestplate was never intended to be a chestplate at all. Rather, it is a broken fragment of an arm bracer, from the time of giants.

info.name: Gravity
info.lore: No one knows how this extremely dense chestplate can even logically exist. It is almost paradoxical in nature, and affects its wearers in unfathomable ways.

info.name: Boreal-Patterned Aegis
info.lore: Infused with the classical magicks of fire, water, and thunder, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Elysium-Engraved Aegis
info.lore: Dedicated to a place of courage revered by all warriors, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Twilight-Gilded Cloak
info.lore: An ephemeral moment in time captured by sheer force of magic, this ornately-crafted cloak is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Hetusol
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] The make of this massive cloak is unlike anything seen before among the provinces. Foreign images shift and melt in ethereal projections within the inside.

info.name: Katoa's Warmth
info.lore: Brilliantly golden as the crops from the humble farm, its mere presence fills stomachs and brings comfort, but only to those who are modest and generous.

info.name: Leo
info.lore: This thick skinned jacket, imbued with the courage of a thousand lion hearts, will grant the user massive protection from all who target them.

info.name: Libra
info.lore: Before the invention of magical weight detectors, there was a giant pair of public scales in Cinfras. Instead of being thrown away, they were reforged to be a formidable piece of armour.

info.name: Discoverer
info.lore: Wealth and riches...but at what cost?

info.name: Masochist
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Matryoshka Shell
info.lore: The armor worn by the enigmatic Matryoshka Idol. It appears to have a nearly uncountably high number of inlets and sockets set inside.

info.name: Millennium
info.lore: Cosmic energy permeates this deceptively dull-looking chestplate, having been crafted with stardust from a comet that only passes over Wynn every 1000 years.

info.name: Bob's Battle Chestplate
info.lore: This battered chestplate was once worn by the legendary Wynnic protector, Bob, during the fearsome corrupted sieges before he gave it away to an old friend. An air of melancholy hangs over it.

info.name: Mummy's Rag
info.lore: The accursed mummy once wore this robe as a great pharaoh of the desert. It has long since rotted, leaving only a cursed shell of its former greatness.

info.name: Nemract's Ruin
info.lore: This chestplate was originally created as a memorial ornament to the lost lives of Ancient Nemract before being reforged into a powerful piece of armor for Nemract's guard.

info.name: Petrichor
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Puppeteer
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Tisaun's Valor
info.lore: Tisaun, a warrior tasked to fend off a corrupted siege alone, could find only a thin shirt and rusted spear to use before the attack. He defeated all 1000 enemies without taking a scratch, and his bravery infused his gear with that same strength.

info.name: Ragni's Mail
info.lore: One of the few remaining standard issue mails that were used against the first hordes to emerge from the infamous portal over 1000 years ago.

info.name: Enhanced Copper Plate
info.lore: The merchant insists that the wear and oxidation on the armor "is a feature."

info.name: Sawdust
info.lore: Once cursed by a druid who had his grove chopped away by a greedy Villager, it was then purified and mass-produced for sale as armor, to the druid's utter disappointment.

info.name: Taurus
info.lore: The hide of the Touroto, an almost invincible Bull-like creature, is said to be pierced only by the horn of the Touroto itself, making it extremely valuable.

info.name: Alternator
info.lore: Llevigar's schools of wizardry are notorious for their difficult training regimens. These leg plates, forcing users to balance spellcasting with direct combat, are often cited as the tipping point for successful wizards.

info.name: Antimony
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Asphyxia
info.lore: A condition of severely deficient supply of oxygen to the body that arises from abnormal breathing; practitioners that abuse specific magic combos are often found incapacitated by said condition.

info.name: Bridge of the Divide
info.lore: These leggings hold the interest of many researching the corruption, as they are the only documented case of a non-corrupt fusion of dark and light energy, made of pure twilight.

info.name: Chained Pixels
info.lore: Materials of all sorts have been lashed together in this crude, blocky set of leggings. From darksteel to leather to rotting wood, each part is a perfect square. It has, so far, been impossible to recreate.

info.name: Conductor
info.lore: Using an unorthodox method of smithing, these copper leggings are insulated with an extremely conductive blend of liquid to improve electrical discharge.

info.name: Crystal
info.lore: Forged on Mage Island, the sparkling liquid-like armour is as hard as obsidian, but light and fluid as water. It glistens with the magic of the ocean winds.

info.name: Gold Digger
info.lore: "With the corruption seemingly tied to the emeralds dug by the Roots, people thought gold was the next best thing, the idiots." -Gerald, Retired Miner

info.name: Knee
info.lore: "I thought aiming for the legs would disable the enemy. Turns out they can drag themselves with their arms just as quick." -Therck, Ragni Soldier 3rd Division

info.name: Spinneret
info.lore: "...Most of their vital organs, however, are located in the bulbous abdomen. If you've enough crushing force with your weapon, it may be a quicker alternative for the kill. ..." -Admiral Aegis' Guide To Nivla Threats, Chapter 3

info.name: Dark Shroud
info.lore: Wearing this deceptively simple shroud causes the user to fade into the shadows, sometimes flickering out of existence for a moment.

info.name: Darkiron Scrap
info.lore: Despite being only an impure scrap of the normally sturdy blackiron, these heavy leggings still have extreme defensive capabilities.

info.name: Dead Sands
info.lore: Found in the middle of the Almuj desert, these greaves seem to slowly poison all life around them. Theorists suggest they were the handiwork of a wicked necromancer, though the truth is not known.

info.name: Gemini
info.lore: The gods of air and thunder, frustrated with being physically insubstantial alone, decided to band together to forge the ultimate leggings of defense.

info.name: Greaves of the Veneer
info.lore: Forged from mystic, previously unknown metals revealed in the deepest dwarven mining site to date, these sleek, glowing greaves are believed to be utterly indestructible.

info.name: Abyss-Imbued Leggings
info.lore: Steeped in the deepest energies of the Ahms region void, these ornately-crafted leggings are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Chaos-Woven Greaves
info.lore: With threads of fundamentally opposing magic delicately woven together, these ornately-crafted greaves are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Hephaestus-Forged Greaves
info.lore: Consecrated by Qira herself with blessings unknown to all but her, these ornately-crafted leggings are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Holy Greaves
info.lore: Many blacksmiths have tried to craft their products in this armor's image, but none so far have been able to capture the brilliance of these Bovemist-blessed greaves.

info.name: Kelight's Shield
info.lore: Used by the Temple of the Legends' strongest guard, the shielded plating is enchanted with a powerful ward to stave off the effects of the corruption.

info.name: Kratke
info.lore: Spurred on by a drunken bet, the great Thanos smith Kratke improved a pair of leggings from a rival that were once thought to be perfection.

info.name: Lemon Legs
info.lore: Due to an unfortunate accident where he choked on a lemon, an unremarkable mercenary became a laughing stock. He later managed to shed the title, as he left no one alive who remembered the name.

info.name: Opulenity
info.lore: Made of an uncommonly used fabric called denim, these fashionable leggings exude style and elegance. Surely wearing them would bring you luck?

info.name: Post-Ultima
info.lore: These leggings are the last remaining piece of a historical set of armor, created with such power as to be thought impossible long ago.

info.name: Ohms' Rage
info.lore: These ancient, spark-coursing greaves are all that remains of the great thunder mage Ohms' favorite golem familiar after a dark force turned it against its masters.

info.name: Enhanced DuskShield
info.lore: They look extremely bulky and uncomfortable...do they have a right to call it "enhanced"?

info.name: Enhanced Pickpockets
info.lore: Aside from the added plating, they look more or less intact. Somehow, that doesn't surprise you.

info.name: Sagittarius
info.lore: The hide of the centaur is extraordinarily magical in the right hands. It is told to allow the user to gain the swiftness of the horse, but also leaves them vulnerable to hard hitting attacks.

info.name: Vaward
info.lore: A once-great hero left behind these sturdy, reliable greaves, trusting those after her to be able to use their power to protect others, should they don them. Her courage fuels their wearers.

info.name: Winter's Essence
info.lore: These pure, snow-white leggings are rumored to have been crafted by the legendary ice mage Theorick. The people of Nesaak view them as cursed, seeking to destroy them in a bid to stop the endless winter surrounding them.

info.name: Almuj's Walker
info.lore: There used to be a constant battle between Almuj's thieves over these feather-light, gold-plated boots, until one day they were stolen by an unknown pickpocket and never seen again.

info.name: Anchoryl
info.lore: Despite being a much smaller settlement compared to the mighty citadel of Rodoroc, the dwarven smiths of Thanos still can forge mighty products, such as these heavy diamond-alloy boots.

info.name: Audacity
info.lore: A powerful mental curse surrounds these boots, inciting uncontrollable rage into the wearers, as well as the power to enact it upon others.

info.name: Bad Wolf
info.lore: The runic message carved on these enigmatic boots cover hundreds of different languages, many of them disused, but what has been translated seems to describe a disaster soon to arrive to the world.

info.name: Broken Balance
info.lore: Torn scraps of metal line the inside of these boots. They provide no protection, instead forcing a constant adrenaline rush while worn.

info.name: Capricorn
info.lore: During a spiritual journey to Kato temple, the sage Capian was presented with powerful spiritual boots with the intention to be used for peaceful magic, and not hard combat.

info.name: Cyclo
info.lore: A centuries-old storm spirit was banished to these tight boots for his destructive actions. His fury empowers those who wear them with the great force of a raging cyclone.

info.name: Mud
info.lore: "Some pigmen snuffle through dirt for things to eat. We dig up that soil to plant our crops in; it's always full of life." -Thomas, Ravine Village Resident

info.name: Stingy
info.lore: "You should see when the spiders fight over a meal. It looks ridiculous, legs flailing everywhere!" -Captain Enduyn, Ragni Legion 1st Division

info.name: Disco
info.lore: Recovered from a corrupted soldier who wore them, it was found dancing instead of attacking those around it. Even after it was killed, it jostled and jerked around like a dancing puppet.

info.name: Giant Step
info.lore: Found in a mystically-charged Giant ruin, these snug boots recall fond memories, incite calmness, and provide comfort for the wearer.

info.name: Gaea-Hewn Boots
info.lore: Forged in direct tribute to the earth and its aspects, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Hephaestus-Forged Sabatons
info.lore: Honoring a mythical dwarven smith lost to the legends, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

info.name: Hunger
info.lore: Forgotten long ago, these boots curse the wearer with an endless hunger.

info.name: Boreal
info.lore: The last known crafts of Theorick before his fall in battle were pieces of armour crafted out of pure ice, all of which have melted save for these shimmering boots. The coldest gales and most suffocating heat nurture and repair the wearer instead of being stifling or deadly.

info.name: Crusade Sabatons
info.lore: One of the very few physically-powerful artifacts of the Villagers, these boots were used in the initial crusades against the Green-skins, to overpower the Orcs via raw physical might. Though effective, they have not seen use in a long time.

info.name: Dawnbreak
info.lore: Many prophecies foretell of new eras. Most are fabricated or proven false in time. One passed through the Dogun caverns, however, tells of a dawn soon to break, in which the earth shall run red and return to flame. Fanatical sects whisper the coming of a new demonic god.

info.name: Galleon
info.lore: Forged with the raw powers of both the earth and the sea, these boots were initially an attempt at creating a method of foot-travel over the seas. Despite the spectacular failure of that application, they remain a formidable and reliable set of armor.

info.name: Moontower
info.lore: For the belief of the cosmos defilement, the moon was noted to remain unchanged. Those with this belief live only for the light of the moon, desperately seeking to maintain it through means that would only darken the soul of the most devout. Such from them comes the word lunacy.

info.name: Resurgence
info.lore: An antique passed from the Caritat wreckage into the hands of the outcast elves of Efilim. So to honor the memory of the selfless family as inspired their self-imposed exile, their strongest healing spells were imbued into it, and sent to those who needed them most.

info.name: Revenant
info.lore: Those whose souls are lost to the Canyon of the Lost eternally seek form. They inhabit those who wear these boots, unknowingly dragging the soul of the wearer into their ranks if worn for too long, leaving a wandering husk.

info.name: Slayer
info.lore: Many artifacts are found to incite rage in the wearer, and wizards old and new alike conjecture as to the purpose of them. Very few increase the latent abilities of the wearers to ensure havoc, and none to such a degree as these boots.

info.name: Stardew
info.lore: Wybels have a strange attraction to cosmic magic, and many an owner will find them staring through the window at night. One, however, claims to have seen her Wybel making something out of white stardust. The abode was robbed shortly after, and the supposed item gone missing without confirmation of its existence.

info.name: Warchief
info.lore: Sheer strength exudes from these Orcish relics, simple sandals ill-fitting to humans or Villagers. Enchanted with power and rage rather than magic, the strength that is provided when they are worn is unparalleled.

info.name: Meanderthal
info.lore: These boots were retrieved from a frozen man, uncovered on an expedition to Mt. Wynn. It is believed that the man had been wandering the world before his death.

info.name: Memento
info.lore: All those who wear these enchanted boots deposit a single fond memory into them. They are forgotten forever, but wearing them recalls every memory within vividly.

info.name: Abysso Galoshes
info.lore: Rumored to be crafted from a Dernic stone, these sinister boots radiate extremely powerful dark energy. They have absorbed the power of the raging seas in their time locked in Sarnfic.

info.name: Sodeta Boots
info.lore: These boots were standard issue to members of the prestigious, and now disbanded, Sodeta Guild, and given as a gift to the owners of Delnar Mansion one day.

info.name: Nether's Scar
info.lore: Forged directly from the bloody red stone mined from the Nether, they were locked away for fear of inciting insanity in those who wore them.

info.name: Omnitread Boots
info.lore: Plated with enchanted metals, these magic-warding boots allow faster travel over nearly any solid surface.

info.name: Passus Lux
info.lore: A brilliant relic supposedly originating from the Realm of Light, the creators of these strangely shaped boots are completely unknown.

info.name: Cerid's Ingenuity
info.lore: One of the master tinkerer Cerid's greatest inventions, these odd gear-laced boots clink and chime with the sound of clockworks keeping its powerful magic dynamos constantly running.

info.name: Enhanced Coalwalkers
info.lore: Even ignoring the numerous scorches all over, these boots hardly look any better.

info.name: Diving Boots I
info.lore: Just a test item.

info.name: Diving Boots II
info.lore: Just a test item.

info.name: Diving Boots III
info.lore: Just a test item.

info.name: Scorpio
info.lore: The carapace of the common Maexi pet fire scarabs, while alone, only cause minor burns to the touch. However, when woven together, they produce a variety of cumulative effects.

info.name: Seven-League Boots
info.lore: Bending the fabric of reality to allow the wearer to take massive strides, these boots are rumored to contain rogue djinni to power them.

info.name: Stalagmites
info.lore: Although these boots are crafted from corrupted stone, they do not exhibit any corruptive effects on their wearers. Speculation abounds as to the reason.

info.name: Steamjet Walkers
info.lore: A rogue inventor stole the plans for a steam jet booster from Corkus and reverse engineered them onto a set of boots. While effective, they are dangerous, prone to catastrophic failure.

info.name: Ventus Tail
info.lore: Fashioned from the cut tails of the now extinct Venti, these nearly immaterial boots are light as air and crackle with lightning.

info.name: Virgo
info.lore: These common leather boots were once owned by a barbarian with no magical prowess. Instead of enchanting it, he coated the soles in corrupted shards to punish those who opposed him.

info.name: Summa
info.lore: An auxiliary power core of the powerful TERA-4M Mining robot line. It controls the robots by giving the bearer a compulsion to break new grounds and progress further without heed.

info.name: Concentration
info.lore: The forger of this ring had to endure 30 long days of smelting various metals only found in the ocean. A single mistake would ruin the creation. The mystic metals are said to seep into the wearers skin to gently replenish their resolve.

info.name: Black Catalyst
info.lore: Even simply looking at these odd rings gives way to a compulsion to wear two of them, despite all better judgement.

info.name: Field
info.lore: "After the Nivla forest fire, I'm glad the corrupteds haven't thought to try and burn the Detlas Suburbs." -Sergeant Klafson, Detlas Legion

info.name: Spider Ring
info.lore: "Crawly things. They crawl on the mushrooms. Mushrooms shouldn't be crawly!" -Yahya, Mushroom Man

info.name: Intensity
info.lore: The runes carved into this simple gold ring translate into various words meaning power. It amplifies elemental energies in inexplicable ways.

info.name: Kaze
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] Gentle spirits of the wind attract themselves to the brilliant jewels slotted into this ring, bringing peace to its wearers and those around them.

info.name: Bronze Basic Ring
info.lore: This ring is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

info.name: Diamond Fiber Ring
info.lore: This masterpiece of a ring utilizes powerful electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Wearing it, you can feel a deep connection to the ground below.

info.name: Diamond Fusion Ring
info.lore: This mighty ring is the crown jewel amongst elemental rings. Wearing it, your knowledge is no longer limited to a few elements.

info.name: Diamond Hydro Ring
info.lore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this ring on your finger, you could catch a gnat without looking.

info.name: Diamond Solar Ring
info.lore: The device forged into this flawless ring draws all heat from its surrounding. Though it almost burns, you can feel your abilites enhance.

info.name: Diamond Static Ring
info.lore: The heavy electrical impulses coming from this ring would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is pure power. A true masterpiece of engineering.

info.name: Diamond Steam Ring
info.lore: Users of this perfect model of Legendary Island's steam-powered ring have reported feeling weightless in combat. The jewel of the ring is a perfectly clear diamond.

info.name: Gold Fiber Ring
info.lore: This improved ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can sense a rhythm with each step...

info.name: Gold Fusion Ring
info.lore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a powerful elemental force in you. Though stronger than the previous model, its true potential stays sealed.

info.name: Gold Hydro Ring
info.lore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant insisted. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

info.name: Gold Solar Ring
info.lore: The device forged into this advanced ring seems to absorb heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your hand...

info.name: Gold Static Ring
info.lore: The strong shock coming from this advanced version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.

info.name: Gold Steam Ring
info.lore: While this model of the Steam Ring is far superior to its predecessor, there still lies the capacity for one more upgrade. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.

info.name: Silver Fiber Ring
info.lore: This crude looking ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.

info.name: Silver Fusion Ring
info.lore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a strong elemental affinity in you. With some improvements to its core, it could become even better...

info.name: Silver Hydro Ring
info.lore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

info.name: Silver Solar Ring
info.lore: The device forged into this simple ring seems to absorb heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...

info.name: Silver Static Ring
info.lore: Though it's hard to touch the plain, mechanical ring without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

info.name: Silver Steam Ring
info.lore: This prototype model of the Steam Ring increases the user's agility in combat. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.

info.name: Lodestone
info.lore: The magical oddity known as lodestone has been studied for years as an active counterpart to quartz's passive magical properties. Research continues, but it is valuable when creating magical items.

info.name: Martyr
info.lore: A recently married man went off to war wearing this wedding ring. Though he perished in battle, his courage and determination empowers all who wear it.

info.name: Marvel
info.lore: The stellar quality of the coral jewels set into the ring comes from a magical purification process, involving a decade-long soak in mystical Gylia water.

info.name: Old Keeper's Ring
info.lore: Found on the corpse of the oldest shopkeeper of the Gavel province, the engraved text reads 'GREED'.

info.name: Precious
info.lore: A strange magic attracts you to this ring. Maybe you shouldn't tell anyone about its existence?

info.name: Prism
info.lore: The jewel on this ring is found very rarely deep beneath the Light Forest. It has the power to manipulate light itself.

info.name: Rycar's Elation
info.lore: Created from the lip of a wine bottle and dropped in the mystic waters of Lake Gylia, this glass ring seems to follow Rycar's drunken escapades wherever she wanders.

info.name: Rarity
info.lore: Being one of the absolute rarest treasures in the world, it seems to have a mind of its own, only showing itself when a stroke of luck is had.

info.name: Broken Sandust
info.lore: The silver looks rather tarnished...does he expect you to believe that "gem" isn't just a cheap glass bauble?

info.name: Chipped Glitz
info.lore: There are little chips and cracks all over this... was someone trying to break it down for gold?

info.name: Cracked Stonehall
info.lore: It looks like someone tried and failed to improve it. The re-smithing job was obviously rushed...

info.name: Unspeakable
info.lore: The wielders of this cursed glassen bauble are rendered mute. The effect is reversed after the item is removed, but the longer it is worn, the longer the curse remains.

info.name: Binding Brace
info.lore: An oppressively dark aura emanates from this shackle, dampening both the will and magic potency of those that wear it.

info.name: Anarchy
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Buster Bracer
info.lore: A mighty, earth-shatteringly powerful weapon was destroyed for fear of its raw power, and the pieces buried. They were unearthed decades later, and were reforged into various items including this sturdy bracer.

info.name: Call to Concord
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] Reverberating with the bravery and residual strength of fallen Wynn soldiers, every casualty only serves to harden the resolve it instills in the wearer.

info.name: Vitre
info.lore: "They say the eyes are the windows to the soul. That's ridiculous, ocular fluids are primarily opaque." -Ragon, Elemental Researcher

info.name: Ra
info.lore: Undecipherable symbols are carved into this long arm band, though the fiery glow and bright jewel has led archaeologists to believe it is somehow related to the sun.

info.name: Esclavage
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Follow The Wind
info.lore: A lost relic from the Wind Fortress, a mythical stronghold of the Sky Islands that fell into the Void long ago. A small mechanism within the bracelet points towards its place of origin.

info.name: Prowess
info.lore: The runes carved into this simple gold cuff translate into various words meaning mastery. It amplifies the ability of the wearer in mysterious ways.

info.name: Jiandan Handwraps
info.lore: The cloth wraps produced by the canyon Dojo are just that, merely soft cloth. It is left to the users to apply them skillfully in battle, in whatever way they see fit.

info.name: Knucklebones
info.lore: An old Nemract saying is engraved along the metal. "A single toss of the knucklebones can make or break a gambling man."

info.name: Bronze Basic Bracelet
info.lore: This bracelet is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

info.name: Diamond Fiber Bracelet
info.lore: Desired by many of the countless challengers, this bracelet allows you to sense movements over thousands of meters away. It is decorated with rough yet beautiful jewels.

info.name: Diamond Fusion Bracelet
info.lore: This bracelet opens up its wearers spirit, filling it with pure elemental knowledge. The ornaments decorating it are without peer.

info.name: Diamond Hydro Bracelet
info.lore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this bracelet on your arm you could ride a wave with your bare feet.

info.name: Diamond Solar Bracelet
info.lore: The device forged into this perfected bracelet drains all heat from its surroundings. Though it almost burns, you can feel your power growing

info.name: Diamond Static Bracelet
info.lore: The heavy shocks coming from this perfected bracelet would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is the enhancement of power.

info.name: Diamond Steam Bracelet
info.lore: This steam-powered bracelet is sought by many challengers of the Legendary Challenge. They say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.

info.name: Gold Fiber Bracelet
info.lore: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can feel a rhythm with each step...

info.name: Gold Fusion Bracelet
info.lore: This bracelet, decorated with complex ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. Though powerful, there's still a lot to improve.

info.name: Gold Hydro Bracelet
info.lore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

info.name: Gold Solar Bracelet
info.lore: The device forged into this improved bracelet seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your arm...

info.name: Gold Static Bracelet
info.lore: The painful shock coming from this improved version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.

info.name: Gold Steam Bracelet
info.lore: This impressive bracelet is in high demand. Those who have obtained it say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.

info.name: Silver Fiber Bracelet
info.lore: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.

info.name: Silver Fusion Bracelet
info.lore: This bracelet, decorated with simple ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.

info.name: Silver Hydro Bracelet
info.lore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

info.name: Silver Solar Bracelet
info.lore: The device forged into this simple bracelet seems to gather heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...

info.name: Silver Static Bracelet
info.lore: Though it's hard to touch the simple, mechanical bracelet without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

info.name: Silver Steam Bracelet
info.lore: Users who have worn this early model of the Steam Bracelet have reported that they have felt "one with the wind" while wearing it.

info.name: Momentum
info.lore: This golden cuff has an odd time dilation effect surrounding it, slowing all movements significantly, but multiplying the force of impact to a significant degree.

info.name: Anya's Penumbra
info.lore: "The lightest light will never defeat the darkest dark. Only those who understand both can survive."

info.name: Pandemonium
info.lore: Power, but at what cost?

info.name: Remikas' Authority
info.lore: This plain-looking silver bracer is one of the last surviving heirlooms of the first Gavelian king, to be passed down to his heirs. The shimmering metal is said to contain Remikas' soul within it.

info.name: Used Wolf Paw
info.lore: It looks more like a dog paw to you, but you don't feel like risking your life arguing with the merchant.

info.name: Durum's Serenity
info.lore: Carried by the Durum Protector, this small necklace holds but an ounce of the vibrance and life of the Durum Isles.

info.name: Adder Stone
info.lore: Aldorei charms are often shared and tinkered with by gifted Elves within the commune. Though simple, the stones blessed by elven magic provide soothing energy to the wearer.

info.name: Witherhead's Talisman
info.lore: "My dear boy should never have to go through the horrors of losing a mother like that." -Momo, adoptive mother of Bob

info.name: Gospel
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Contrast
info.lore: The runes carved onto the gold beads strung along this simple necklace translate into various words meaning variance. It provides many abilities though unexplainable means.

info.name: Hexed Amulet
info.lore: Although the warlock's curse placed upon this simple, Olux-crafted charm will reduce the abilities of the wearer significantly, its original luck-bolstering properties still are in place.

info.name: Bronze Basic Necklace
info.lore: This necklace is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

info.name: Diamond Fiber Necklace
info.lore: This ultimate version of a necklace was given to less than a handful of adventurers. Once on your neck, you can communicate with the ground below as if you grew roots.

info.name: Diamond Fusion Necklace
info.lore: Unlike any other invention this necklace enhances your power and understanding of the elements tenfold. The colorful jewels used are almost dizzying you.

info.name: Diamond Hydro Necklace
info.lore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said and every word was true. With this necklace equipped, you could hear the ocean whisper.

info.name: Diamond Solar Necklace
info.lore: The masterpiece of a necklace gathers all heat from its surrounding. It is fed to its wearer to maximize the strength of attacks.

info.name: Diamond Static Necklace
info.lore: The lethal amount of electricity emmited from this often desired necklace fails to kill you, as its pure energy runs through your veins.

info.name: Diamond Steam Necklace
info.lore: This necklace is the pinnacle of steam-powered technology. Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from the necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all.

info.name: Gold Fiber Necklace
info.lore: This improved version of a bracelet utilizes rare electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You notice a rhythm with each step...

info.name: Gold Fusion Necklace
info.lore: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses advanced nano-technology to boost its users elemental abilities. Though powerful, there are still a few flaws to be fixed.

info.name: Gold Hydro Necklace
info.lore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

info.name: Gold Solar Necklace
info.lore: The device forged into this advanced necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your neck...

info.name: Gold Static Necklace
info.lore: The strong shock coming from this improved version of the necklace is a small price for its strength, but it has yet to reach its peak.

info.name: Gold Steam Necklace
info.lore: The jewel hanging from this necklace is said to be weightless. While still very powerful, its full potential has yet to be achieved.

info.name: Legendary Medallion
info.lore: This medallion marks its wearer as a true champion. It is awarded to those who have put an unnecessary amount of time into attempting the Legendary Challenge.

info.name: Silver Fiber Necklace
info.lore: This crude looking necklace utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains quiet.

info.name: Silver Fusion Necklace
info.lore: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.

info.name: Silver Hydro Necklace
info.lore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

info.name: Silver Solar Necklace
info.lore: The device forged into this basic necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warm sting when holding it.

info.name: Silver Static Necklace
info.lore: Though it's hard to touch the plain, tech-enhanced necklace without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

info.name: Silver Steam Necklace
info.lore: Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from this necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all. However, the necklace's mechanisms seem incomplete.

info.name: Luminis
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Master
info.lore: Although not truly magical by any means, the sheer craftsmanship of this ornate broach makes its wearers feel skillful.

info.name: Abyssal Amulet
info.lore: Used by the Order of the Abyss to aid their summoning rituals, it contains a strange, fiery energy. It has ties with a terrible demon...

info.name: Altum Spatium
info.lore: Even looking at this pendant strains your eyes. Should it even exist?

info.name: Royal Blazing Amulet
info.lore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It glows with a comforting warmth.

info.name: Royal Cyclone Amulet
info.lore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It whistles with an invigorating tune.

info.name: Royal Dusty Amulet
info.lore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It shines with a powerful strength.

info.name: Royal Shocking Amulet
info.lore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It crackles with a chaotic energy.

info.name: Royal Stormy Amulet
info.lore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It pulsates with a calming aura.

info.name: Wynnter Fair 2016 Souvenir
info.lore: Thank you for participating in the 2016 Wynnter Fair!

info.name: Wynnter Fair 2017 Souvenir
info.lore: Thank you for participating in the 2017 Wynnter Fair!

info.name: Wynnterfest 2016 Souvenir
info.lore: Thank you for participating in Wynnterfest 2016!

info.name: Necklace of a Thousand Storms
info.lore: Sealed away by the Avos of the old days to prevent it from falling into the wrong hands, this necklace was enchanted to strengthen its wearers spiritual link to nature itself.

info.name: Oyster
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Planet Healer
info.lore: The jewels in this necklace naturally draw darkness and corruption into its wearer, purifying the land around them at the cost of their own life.

info.name: Ensa's Faith
info.lore: The scholar-priest Ensa created this pendant as a personal prayer while his home was under siege. It is rumored to hold the key to enlightenment, but it is unknown as to how.

info.name: Shatterglass
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] This small, rough-crafted pendant is the only known magic artifact of the Orcs. It incites destructive tendencies within the wearer.

info.name: Stellar
info.lore: Elementally attuned gemstones are melded together to form the singular marvel found on this pendant. Despite the violent smithing process, the jewel is utterly flawless.

info.name: Tenuto
info.lore: This strange pendant has been known to dilate time around the wearer, slowing their movements while greatly augmenting their power.

info.name: Helm Splitter
info.lore: One of Skien's many deadly weapons. This warhammer, despite the massive weight of the hammerhead, was able to be swung by Skien fast enough to be a blur.

info.name: Kahontsi Ohstyen
info.lore: Wielded by the chief of the Tromsian jungle's zombie tribes, the augmentable crystals within it focus natural elemental energies to intense levels.

info.name: Braker
info.lore: Seems like the name is misspelled a little bit.

info.name: Bedruthan
info.lore: Stone shorn from mountains by the roiling sea gathered on the shores of Llevigar one day, washed onto the sand in the shape of a massive spear. It was taken as an omen, and the stones were forged into a true weapon.

info.name: Blade of Purity
info.lore: The creator of this polished white blade insists that its true power will never be unlocked, for only those who are not influenced by the elements of the world know truly how to utilize it.

info.name: Chaleur
info.lore: This blackiron blade was left to sear in the desert for months on end by a fanatical berserker. It burned him alive as he cut down those who opposed him.

info.name: Clash Hook
info.lore: The wear on this humble war pick's blade has only made it more effective in combat, allowing its users to make unexpected parries of opponents' attacks by hooking and hitting through the weapon.

info.name: Corpse
info.lore: "Catch a fresh-raised corrupted, it's like catching a soldier without his morning coffee. Stumbly and unfocused." -Enzan, Retired Ragni Soldier

info.name: Skull Breaker
info.lore: "Even a corrupted would get crushed by one of these!" -Roche 'Stone-thrower' Diamant, Ragni Citizen

info.name: Maul
info.lore: "If you squish a spider egg, sometimes little spiders pop out. So, squish the whole area instead!" -Captain Fenor, Detlas Legion

info.name: Sting
info.lore: "I swear on my life those spiders were covered in spikes! Go out there, see if I'm wrong!" -Suri, Elemental Researcher

info.name: Cathedral
info.lore: "The gravestone for the brother of that man, Sayleros? For whatever reason, it didn't have a proper name on it." -Sacre, Saint's Row Priest

info.name: Sanies
info.lore: "Can anyone else understand that General Graken? Because I can't." -Commander Takan, Nemract Militia

info.name: Fierce Thunder
info.lore: Every time this spear hits an enemy, a sharp electrical jolt hits the users hands that forces powerful lightning to release.

info.name: Fierte
info.lore: Only the most honourable warriors of Gavel's army are presented the trident shaped spear, forged from the rarest metal from the molten heights.

info.name: Fissure
info.lore: Dwarven folklore tells of this mighty maul, used by gods to break mountains, shape continents, and crack the earth to form caverns.

info.name: Infused Hive Spear
info.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this spear has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its tip shimmers in a spectrum of colors.

info.name: Harwrol
info.lore: The runes carved onto the spear shift appearance so quickly as to be illegible, but those who wield it supposedly will learn their meaning.

info.name: Ignition
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] Forged with flaming scales shorn from Ozoth, the fabled Golden Ninja of the Canyon of the Lost hunted his prey relentlessly using this lightweight, yet harder than steel, polearm.

info.name: Legendary Smasher
info.lore: Many have tried to duplicate the properties of this spear, but very few have succeeded in enchanting a spearhead with explosive magic that does not cause the spear itself to explode.

info.name: Alkatraz
info.lore: Soul-locking magic is one outlawed by Gavellian governments, only used by the most insidious and cruel of mages. One such enchantment looms dormant in this mundane-looking maul. Continued usage of the weapon threatens to release it upon the wielder, permanently binding them to the weapon.

info.name: Apocalypse
info.lore: Forged from the tooth of the fallen one, this spear was bargained to a human for his soul, not knowing that the weapon itself would claim all life.

info.name: Collapse
info.lore: Despite the light weight of the weapon, the spearhead has been made from incredibly dense cosmic stone. A strong enough impact can directly destroy matter. Due to this danger, it is sought after to be destroyed.

info.name: Guardian
info.lore: A vow of protection hangs over this spear, now inhabited by the spirit of a legendary heroine. Even simply a glimpse of the burning blade will instill a feeling of protection and security, and that feeling will hold true if one is brave enough to wield it.

info.name: Hero
info.lore: Enigmatically, this weapon will only show itself to those who believe themselves to be worth nothing, or to be weak. While utilizing this weapon will greatly strengthen one's resolve, it will disappear when it is no longer needed, going to the next wielder.

info.name: Idol
info.lore: Intricate carvings and images, almost like that of a totem pole, cover the shaft of this marvelous trident, dredged up from the Seavale Reef. Foreign magics heighten the senses of its user in battle, but also instills a longing for the ocean. Many have succumbed to this urge and drowned themselves.

info.name: Thrundacrack
info.lore: The raw aspect of thunder, though claimed to be harnessed by a mage in a wand, has only been truly tamed by this mighty blade. Combined electric and life-draining magic intertwine and bring forth the truest, most frightening power of all Thunder.

info.name: Maltic's Old Spear
info.lore: This short spear was the first weapon to be produced by the villagers for sale. They are old, but strong.

info.name: Olux's Prized Spear
info.lore: This expertly crafted spear was forged by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shines brilliantly in even the weakest sunlight.

info.name: Proxima
info.lore: This spear is bright enough that it can cause blindness if you look directly at it. Its immense power is limited by its weight; the weapon is nearly impossible to lift.

info.name: Pulsar
info.lore: The density of this weapon is almost immeasurable. Despite being light and easy to wield, the spear seems to have its own gravitational pull, slowly dragging enemies closer and making it nearly impossible to put down.

info.name: Remikas' Righteousness
info.lore: Despite this mace never seeing use by Remikas, it was seen as a symbol of the might of his rule over Gavel. Its true abilities in battle have never been seen.

info.name: Rikter
info.lore: Named for an ancient Wynnic word for "Earthquake", this mighty battle hammer causes the very bones of struck enemies to rattle and heave as though the earth itself was splitting under their feet.

info.name: Upgraded Archpriest
info.lore: It seems stronger at first glance, but upon closer inspection the blade is rather...soft?

info.name: Upgraded Steel Buster
info.lore: It is significantly heavier than usual...you can't tell if that is good or not, in this case.

info.name: Scythe
info.lore: A psychopath claiming herself to be Death incarnate used this dark-bladed scythe on a killing spree that lasted over a year. It reaped hundreds of lives, including her own.

info.name: The Berserk
info.lore: Forged from unbreakable obsidian eras ago, this heavy hammer has crushed many foes with a single swing.

info.name: The Eviscerator
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Tidebinder
info.lore: This mysterious, half-liquid trident apparently holds the secret magics to control the ocean's ebb and flow. It is incapable of touching solid ground.

info.name: Tisaun's Proof
info.lore: The wear upon this broken old battle spear does not affect its ability in battle. The souls of a thousand fallen warriors resound within it.

info.name: Toaster
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\] This peculiar weapon was once wielded by the firey warrior Igbar, who used it to great effect in nether-endurance competitions.

info.name: Zephra Shredder
info.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and sheer rage intertwine to create a fearsome sight, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for total destruction.

info.name: Blade of Shade
info.lore: The fabled weapon of the titular dark Assassin, the blade's small stature hides its true powers. Shadows undulate about the hilt.

info.name: Slider
info.lore: The spelling seems to have been botched.

info.name: Alazarin
info.lore: This bloody palette knife was used to kill only two people before it was abandoned - a killer who broke into a great artist's home, and the artist who struck the blow.

info.name: Almuj's Daggers
info.lore: The reigning king of thieves in Almujs underworld would brandish this golden dagger to his enemies so fast, you wouldnt even realise your wallet was now missing.

info.name: Arma Gauntlet
info.lore: Stories say that should anyone wield both of these fearsome gauntlets in battle, they will become unkillable in a fight. The second gauntlet, however, has never been found.

info.name: Black
info.lore: Hewn from the great obsidian spires surrounding the massive Nether gate, this fiercely-hooked dagger absorbs light and magic energy alike to create a desolate void wherever it is wielded.

info.name: Brass Brand
info.lore: Built by Cerid to accrue raw static charge from the surroundings and direct it at opponents, the blade's chief failing is that the wielder is not rendered immune to their own discharge as intended.

info.name: Wybel Paw
info.lore: Even reduced to just the bones, you can't help but feel bad for the poor thing this paw came from.

info.name: Chakram
info.lore: Despite appearing as a basic blade when held, strange spiritual magic changes its form into a sharp, ring-like cutting edge when used to attack. Only one person was known to master the weapon's abilities.

info.name: Defibrillator
info.lore: "The first time I saw one of those zombies I nearly had a heart attack! The blighters are terrifying." -Rynend, Maltic Citizen

info.name: Fangs
info.lore: "Not every spider is venomous, but do you really want to get bitten by them all to figure out which are?" -Alvin, Nivla Forest Resident

info.name: Abolition
info.lore: "Those bloody zombies don't kip down at night, what makes you think a curfew might bally-well help?" -General Graken, Nemract Militia

info.name: Styx's Grab
info.lore: "Never wish to see a dead loved one again. In this day and age, they'll come back to see you." -Mylo, Nemract Conscript

info.name: Dislocater
info.lore: Often, the leader of brute gangs would use this dagger to threaten his followers into making sure they did not fail him.

info.name: Flameshot Hilt
info.lore: Found abandoned in the ruins of the Doguns, these odd weapons are designed to shoot jets of sheer flame instead of hitting enemies traditionally. They are in terrible disrepair, and none know how to fix them.

info.name: Infused Hive Dagger
info.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this dagger has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It leaves afterimages that pulsate in a spectrum of colors.

info.name: Impulse
info.lore: Prolonged exposure to the corruption may cause sudden bursts of madness in soldiers. To assure themselves of their sanity, some have even begun to play tricks on their brethren.

info.name: Influence
info.lore: This knife does not belong in your hands... yet somehow it feels right at home.

info.name: Iron Knuckle
info.lore: These bulky-looking gauntlets are actually extremely lightweight, being created of a magical elf-blessed iron alloy blend.

info.name: Ivory
info.lore: The holy blade of the House of Talor was crafted of pure unicorn horns, and consecrated by a hundred priests. Evil spirits are driven away by its mere presence.

info.name: Locrian
info.lore: Skien's trust in others was shattered permanently by the wielder of this dagger, who fell to the corruption and attacked his legion during a great corrupted siege.

info.name: Archangel
info.lore: The unwieldy, yet imposing stature of this massive sickle strikes awe into those who view it. Those who have the will to wield it, however, seem to garner respect from all those around them, as though they had become a god.

info.name: Cataclysm
info.lore: Despite the existence of the Nether Portal, few believe that it is possible to open such rifts with sheer force alone. None believe that a tool with enough power to accomplish such a monumental feat could exist. And yet...

info.name: Grimtrap
info.lore: Found at the site of the Caritat Mansion, this simple-looking glove is bathed in dark presence. It wracks those who wear it with pain, and instills the belief that the only way to end the pain is not to remove the item, but to inflict that same torment upon all others.

info.name: Inferno
info.lore: The Dogun God Garaheth was actually an immense fire demon occupying the bowels of Molten Heights. Although unwise, the Dwarves forged a demonic dagger using his tooth in celebration of his slaughter.

info.name: Nirvana
info.lore: Spiritual enlightenment is a goal that many monks hope to one day grasp the barest glimpse of, often thought to be a goal that must be worked towards over a lifetime. Holding this polished, translucent blade will instantly induce that lofty state until it is let go.

info.name: Nullification
info.lore: The diminutive stature of this item belies its abilities. Absorbing and expelling magical energy in precise bursts, it protects the user from all manner of attacks while punishing those who dare strike.

info.name: Weathered
info.lore: A relic of the past in Time Valley was weathered down to a dagger by the sheer power of the wind. When used in battle, mysterious intertwined wind and time magic give it no physical presence.

info.name: Olux's Prized Dagger
info.lore: This expertly crafted dagger was smithed by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It can chop through even the thickest of the swamp's clay with ease.

info.name: Reaper of Soul
info.lore: A grave digger uncovered this blade from the resting place of a notorious pirate that pillaged the islands of the ocean for four decades.

info.name: Rewind
info.lore: Time moves in strange ways around this translucent blade, speeding and slowing, starting and stopping, with no observable reasoning or pattern.

info.name: Upgraded Whisper
info.lore: The blade seems sharper than normal, but it also seems rather brittle. The smithing was obviously a hack-job...

info.name: Scorpion
info.lore: This dagger has no blade. Instead, it is layered with the stingers of the Black Shadow Scorpion, which has the ability to vanish entirely from its prey.

info.name: Sitis
info.lore: Wielding it for too long will leave one a dessicated husk, as this dull blade slowly absorbs all liquids around it.

info.name: StabSand
info.lore: The art of endurance fighting is a skill lost to time. However, a thief that to this day has not been caught, imbued this dagger with the very same ability.

info.name: The Divide
info.lore: Once having held unstoppable amounts of magic, being forced to fuse into one form locked away all but the smallest sliver of their power.

info.name: The Exile
info.lore: This indestructible dagger was found floating in the magma of the Molten Heights, with a lament from its exiled smith carved onto the hilt.

info.name: Thrunda Ripsaw
info.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and consuming fury combine to create a deadly aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for utter cataclysm.

info.name: Plague Staff
info.lore: Carried by the Olux Plague Doctor, this simple-looking stick subtly oozes with an unidentifiable substance that is invigorating to the holder, and lethally venomous to anything else.

info.name: Haros' Oar
info.lore: The weathered oar of Haros, the outcast ferryman of Charon's Forsaken Legion. Magical implements have been jury-rigged onto the silver pole, glowing dull out of his bony grasp.

info.name: Stave of the Legends
info.lore: Crafted exclusively by the Temple of the Legends' mages, this stave is honorary to Mages who best the Temple's Grand Magus.

info.name: Bonder
info.lore: It looks like they spelled the name wrong...

info.name: Afterimage
info.lore: This wand is capable of attacks so fast that it appears to flicker in and out of existence. Anyone able to access its full potential will be seen as only a blur to their enemies.

info.name: Ancient Wand
info.lore: It is thought that this primitive wand was used by early man to create the first spells. It is made from a wood that no longer exists.

info.name: Bismuthinite
info.lore: An extremely rare metallic ore only found within the island region of Corkus, it is normally used in decorative dyes. However, a mishap one day caused the discovery of strange and cumulative effects when exposed to traditional magicks.

info.name: Blossom
info.lore: A mystical sapling native to the shores of Mage Island has been fashioned into this simple staff. Even uprooted, you notice its continuous growth.

info.name: Bough of Fir
info.lore: Crafted from Mandragora roots and adorned with decorative wreaths of Elven pines, these wands are utilized in Efilim's solstice festivals to celebrate each passing year of Villager and Elven comradery.

info.name: Cascade
info.lore: A great magical cataclysm at Mage Island brought on by a strange, seemingly disconnected series of events resulted in this wand absorbing nearly uncontrollably high levels of magic.

info.name: Serpent's Kiss
info.lore: "I bet those sewer-dwellers have horrible morning breath." -Folzoy, Maltic Escort

info.name: Sketiq
info.lore: "As much as they're terrifying, at least those lousy skeletons give us lots of bonemeal for the crops!" -Bylvis, Katoa Ranch Farmer

info.name: Iklaj
info.lore: "I am not making this up! That spider teleported ONTO MY FACE!" -Stiba, Elemental Researcher

info.name: Hymn of the Dead
info.lore: "The dead can still hear. I figure a lullaby might help convince them to sleep a bit longer." -Merloni, Saint's Row Priest

info.name: Putrid
info.lore: "Leave us down here to die, why don't you all. Just turn us into another statistic and be done, huh?" -Ragamal, Nemract Sewer Dweller

info.name: Detlas' Legacy
info.lore: One of Detlas buildings was struck by lightning 60 years ago and burnt to the ground, apart from one wooden beam that began to glow. It was fashioned into an exclusive wand for resident mages.

info.name: Diablo
info.lore: One of the most unstable wands known to man, using the bark of the Flerisi trunk it reaps firey destruction upon its enemies.

info.name: Empire Builder
info.lore: This golden staff was recovered from deep within the tombs of Almuj. Nothing else was found in the room except the words 'Beware the user with unlimited imagination'.

info.name: Ethereal
info.lore: Supposedly based off of the wand of master mage Ethe, this wand is plated with magic-focusing jewels and heavy gold, yet somehow remains entirely weightless.

info.name: Faustian Contract
info.lore: Once a contract is formed, and before its details are discussed, a seal is placed on the human's body.

info.name: Gert Super Special Magic Ultistick
info.lore: Well...it is a very pretty-looking stick, but aside from that it just appears to be a plain old stick.

info.name: Glare
info.lore: The blazing sun has been revered by many druidic sects as a god in its own right, and the jewel in this brilliant wand glows with the brightness of their holy star.

info.name: Infused Hive Wand
info.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this wand has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It subtly glows in a spectrum of colors.

info.name: Lunar Spine
info.lore: From the Nether Gate, a shard of cosmic stone was ejected. Its purity was defiled, and the first man to wield it went mad, raving about the fall of the cosmos' beauty.

info.name: Fatal
info.lore: A mage by the name of Lero claims to have harnessed the sheer power of lightning using a magical staff, however, the weapon is very unreliable in a pinch.

info.name: Gaia
info.lore: The Dernel tribes revere various nature deities, each in their own unique fashions. One of the most notable was that of a lost tribe, who fashioned this blossoming stave as tribute to their deity of the earth itself.

info.name: Lament
info.lore: When the lost city of Sarnfic sunk beneath the depths, nothing but the bubbles of screams and this single wand surfaced. When used, you can still hear the towns lament.

info.name: Monster
info.lore: This wand merges with the user on touch, bringing about horrific changes to them. Elongated nails, sharp teeth and the ability to breathe fire are trademarks of the beast.

info.name: Pure
info.lore: Carved directly from the mysterious rock that hit Gavel 50 years ago, this pure white wand glows with cosmic energy unknown.

info.name: Singularity
info.lore: The existence of all things is reflected in the otherworldly jewels of this grand staff, dense enough to have its own gravitational pull. Users have reported their limbs being stretched after usage.

info.name: Warp
info.lore: The notorious and erratic magical inventor Gawrick once attempted to make teleportation scrolls obsolete, by creating items which would allow the user to phase into an ethereal state to move unhindered. He did not account for the physical ramifications of this process, however.

info.name: Morrowind
info.lore: One of many lost artifacts from the legendary Wind Fortress, the engraving appears to be a cryptic clue to where the Fortress fell. "We shall be found among the dark winds of the morrow."

info.name: Olux's Prized Wand
info.lore: This expertly crafted wand was shaped by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shimmers with the purest water from the swamp.

info.name: Nepta Floodbringer
info.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and immense wisdom meld to create a commanding aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for dominion over all.

info.name: Ohms' Wish
info.lore: "If anyone finds this, leave it at my Gale's gravesite. I promised her a memento, too." This inscription is extremely weathered.

info.name: Phoenix Wing
info.lore: The magically rejuvenating properties of phoenix ash were imbued into this grand stave in its creator's bid to gain immortality.

info.name: Prymari
info.lore: This staff was expertly crafted from fragile spun glass, and tinted with various magical foci that bend light into its most raw components.

info.name: Red Candle
info.lore: The flickering flame atop this simple wand is a marvel of magic. It always burns at a comfortable heat, cannot scorch skin even if touched, and never can be snuffed out under any circumstance.

info.name: Reticence
info.lore: Many old mages had to perform lengthy incantations to make potent even their simplest spells. A mage cursed to be mute, however, brought upon a revolution to spellcasting through this simple wand.

info.name: Upgraded Dark Needle
info.lore: The magic in this wand seems much weaker than normal...and there's a rather rude message written on the handle.

info.name: Sage
info.lore: Discipline and experience is channeled into these wands for 10 years in the Bantisu monastery of the canyon, in the hope that they will pass on its teachings to less experienced users.

info.name: Sigil of Existence
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Squall's Breath
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Starburst
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Waves Raiser
info.lore: The mystery of the oceans appearance has eluded scholars for centuries. It is believed that many years ago, warlocks used wands like this one in an attempt to submerge the world.

info.name: Deadeye
info.lore: The weapon of the fearsome lone bandit, Rymek Luke, it is unique in that it is designed to fire small metal rounds instead of more traditional projectiles.

info.name: Stinger
info.lore: If it weren't for that stray mark, this would be spelled correctly...

info.name: Aersectra
info.lore: \[Community Event Winner\]

info.name: Alka Cometflinger
info.lore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and raw potential fuse to create an imposing presence, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for complete obliteration.

info.name: Clairvoyance
info.lore: The powerful psychic energies surrounding this bow are rumored to increase accuracy, though this has not been refuted by any reliable source.

info.name: Cluster
info.lore: Perhaps one is weak. To be ignored. Perhaps two are not much better. But what of five? Ten? Twenty?...

info.name: Crackshot
info.lore: This heavy crossbow forces a strange compulsion in its users when wielded. They will often refuse to even shoot unless entirely certain of a hit.

info.name: Witherhead's Bow
info.lore: Wielded by the master of the Decrepit Sewers Dungeon, the arrows of this bow causes the target's body to slowly wither away.

info.name: Stale
info.lore: "There's never new water flowing into those sewers. It all cycles back into itself...not natural." -Jenprest, Ragni Legion 2nd Division

info.name: Web Spitter
info.lore: "And you thought walking into a cobweb was bad." -Ope, Ragni Botanist

info.name: Damnation
info.lore: "I got a name, known far and wide! Run along, you bandit scum, before you have to learn it the hard way!" -Sayleros' Brother, killed by bandits

info.name: Death's Reach
info.lore: "We'll ensure that under our watch, all your families will be reunited!" -Haros, of the Banished Legion

info.name: Eruption
info.lore: No one expected the WynnExcavation volcanic site to produce any valuable materials, but this heavy, obsidian-blend bow silenced the critics.

info.name: Gale's Force
info.lore: Those who have used this near-weightless bow all seem to tell tales of how they see Gale's spirit fighting alongside them.

info.name: Glacial Crest
info.lore: Used for endurance training on the Icy Islands, this bow forces the wielder's body temperature to drop to near-hypothermic levels.

info.name: Infused Hive Bow
info.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this bow has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its string radiates a spectrum of colors.

info.name: Hellstrand
info.lore: The Order of the Abyss crafted this bow in opposition to the House of Talor's holy relic. Holding it for too long will strain and warp the user's mind.

info.name: Heracul
info.lore: Reconstructed from mere wooden scraps of its former self, this extremely heavy crossbow still contains immense power. It was intended for use with a lost suit of armor, of which only one piece remains.

info.name: Infinity
info.lore: If you reach for ammunition from your quiver, as long as you have a single arrow, you will find you never run out.

info.name: Iron String
info.lore: Many said making a bow out of iron would be slow and wasteful, but the weight of the iron arrow can pierce even stone.

info.name: Az
info.lore: Mysterious runes, held by inexplicable ancient guardians, were once moulded together for study purposes. The experiment went awry, as the runic words Nii, Az, and Ek were combined in a reaction that resulted in the collapse of a civilization.

info.name: Divzer
info.lore: Unruly magics of void and darkness are tamed within this bow's string. While those energies are never to be released, arrows fired from it fire at such blinding speeds so as to phase out of existence when they hit their target.

info.name: Freedom
info.lore: Freedom of soul, mind, and body are forced upon all those that this bow's arrows impact, and freedom of caring from the atrocities that such a dangerous weapon can inflict is given to all those that hold it.

info.name: Grandmother
info.lore: The very first crossbow in existence was claimed to be utterly indestructible, but it is only true to a fault. The item cannot be broken, but solely because all damage to it is instead reflected onto the user. As its age is uncountably ancient, wielders will find themselves rapidly aging and withering away with even a mere touch.

info.name: Ignis
info.lore: This bow, used by the dwarves to land the final blow in the slaughter of Garaheth is extremely powerful. Special, fire resistant gloves must be worn at all times to prevent burns to the user.

info.name: Spring
info.lore: Arrows fired by this bow are pure ice, but when they hit the enemy, burst into magical water, flash-freezing all that it touches. The frost burns will never heal.

info.name: Stratiformis
info.lore: The Elves managed to harness the power of air itself, forming a bow made entirely of air currents, allowing the user to move swift like the wind, but vulnerable to attacks.

info.name: Maelstrom
info.lore: Lost by master sailor Carvel in a massive storm, it was carried all the way out to the city of Selchar, where it was found spewing seafoam and lightning bolts.

info.name: Mesarock Arch
info.lore: The two mesa tribes once were allies until their sacred totems were stolen. Before that time, however, they often shared their talents, and this bow hewn from mesa stone was one such lost craft.

info.name: Olux's Prized Bow
info.lore: This expertly crafted bow was whittled by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its frame was cut from the very toughest tree roots.

info.name: Nemract's Rage
info.lore: A year-long monsoon soaked this Nemract-made bow so much, that it has harnessed the very essence of water.

info.name: Relic
info.lore: Despite being proven unrelated, this enigmatic bow was the lynchpin to beginning the great search for the Relics.

info.name: Return to Ether
info.lore: This enigmatic weapon can suddenly blink out of reality with no warning only to appear exactly where it was left later. Artificers have determined that almost the entire bow, by all known laws of nature and magic, should not exist.

info.name: Upgraded Radiance
info.lore: The craftsmanship on this bow is rather poor. The paint on the "crystals" is chipping...

info.name: Skin Piercer
info.lore: The average bow can boast a range of skills, but unlike this one, not every bow can penetrate through any organic skin, including dragon hide.

info.name: Soundwave
info.lore: This bow's thick string fails to shoot arrows effectively, but instead produces low frequency sound waves that erupt from the source in all directions. The sound can implode the eardrums of an enemy with a single strum.

info.name: Spiritshock
info.lore: Potentially one of the most dangerous weapons in existence. A precise enough shot can destroy the soul of those it hits.

info.name: Thunderbolt
info.lore: This bow has no string. Instead, a thin lightning-like thread is strung upon it. It is said to be limited only by the speed of the user.

info.name: Torrential Tide
info.lore: The tides of the ocean, once bound, became useful magic power sources. They were once utilized for weapons, but to harness the unstable force of the raging sea was considered too dangerous.

info.name: Zero
info.lore: The unstable power within this bow is capable of great destruction, but seems to zero out at the most crucial moments in battle. Only the most skillful archers can wield this weapon with confidence.

info.name: Lower
info.lore: The name has got to be misspelled... It doesn't even make any sense!

info.name: Macabre
info.lore: "Only the most wicked in Gavel could dream of a circumstance as what plagues this Wynn province." -King of Ragni

info.name: Hourglass
info.lore: "I saw that spider queen once. It felt like it was only a matter of time before she found my home, so I moved here." -Babhla, Nivla Bowl Merchant

info.name: Thriller
info.lore: "And no one's going to save us from the beasts about to strike. We've seen horrors stare us in the eyes, and we're fighting for our lives." -Poe, Nemract Sewer Dweller

info.name: Infused Hive Relik
info.lore: Deceptively plain-looking, this relik has been infused with energy from all five known elements. The head gleams in a spectrum of colors.

info.name: Harsh Noise
info.lore: Corkian technology was not the first to create an item that is capable  of recording noise. Artifacts from Time Valley were found to record ambient  sounds and distort them into ear-splitting sonic bursts.

info.name: Olux's Prized Relik
info.lore: This expertly crafted relik was notched by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its feathers and baubles chime with a soothing melody.

info.name: Procrastination
info.lore: ...I'll finish writing this later.
